Dorotheus has thus given the 12 signs dominion over some 30 countries: Manilius has nearer 50 to dispose of, and he differs from Dorotheus and Paulus in making some effort to show that his disposition is not aimless or arbitrary and that reasons exist at least in certain cases for the association of land and sign. Only ten regions, Arabia, Ethiopia, Phrygia, Rhodes, Arcadia, Italy, Carthage, Hammonia, Crete, and the eastern ocean, are clearly allotted to the
